FBIS4-9484 "dreeu080__a94053" FBIS-EEU-94-080-A Daily Report 25 Apr 1994 ANNEX Slovakia Poll Reveals Split Over Meciar's Dismissal Poll Reveals Split Over Meciar's Dismissal AU2504120694 Prague CTK in English 1028 GMT 25 Apr 94 -- FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY AU2504120694 Prague CTK English BFN [Text] Bratislava April 25 (CTK) -- Some 44 percent of Slovaks agree with Vladimir Meciar's dismissal from the premiership, while 39 percent do not, a poll conducted by the Slovak Statistical Office in early April revealed. Some 17 percent are indifferent to the issue, the poll showed. Meciar's fall (on March 11) was welcomed by ethnic Hungarians (80 percent), entrepreneurs (55 percent) and followers of the "dissidents" from Meciar's Movement for a Democratic Slovakia (88 percent).
